Bridge Command
==============

This is the source code for Bridge Command, developed in C++ using the
Irrlicht 3d library.

For more information, see https://www.bridgecommand.co.uk

To compile
----------

For Windows, Visual Studio 2022 (or greater) and Code::Blocks are used
and tested. Project files for both are in the src folder.

For Linux and macOS, CMake is used. Please see the instructions in
src/CompilingLinuxAndMac.txt

Optional build dependencies
---------------------------

These are optional and enable additional features when present:

* GDAL (Geospatial Data Abstraction Library) - enables the S-57 chart
  converter tool (bc-chart-converter). Build with -DWITH_GDAL=ON.
  Install via: apt install libgdal-dev (Linux), brew install gdal (macOS),
  or download from https://gdal.org (Windows).

* OpenAL Soft - enables spatial 3D audio with HRTF support.
  Build with -DWITH_OPENAL=ON. Also requires libsndfile.
  Install via: apt install libopenal-dev libsndfile1-dev (Linux),
  brew install openal-soft libsndfile (macOS).

MMG Physics Model
-----------------

Ships can use the MMG (Maneuvering Modeling Group) physics model for
higher-fidelity handling. Enable per-ship by adding MMGMode=1 to the
ship's boat.ini file. See docs/SHIP_COEFFICIENTS.md for details on
available parameters and per-ship coefficient data.

Chart Converter
---------------

When built with GDAL support, the bc-chart-converter tool converts
S-57 electronic nautical chart files (.000) into Bridge Command world
directories. Usage:

  bc-chart-converter --input <chart.000> --output <world_dir/> [options]

Options:
  --resolution <N>     Heightmap resolution (default: 1025)
  --dem-dir <path>     Directory with Copernicus DEM .tif tiles
  --bathy-dir <path>   Directory with BlueTopo .tif bathymetry tiles

See docs/UPGRADE_PLAN.md for more information.

Wicked Engine Graphics Backend (optional)
-----------------------------------------

An optional modern graphics backend using Wicked Engine is available.
Build with:

  -DWICKED_ENGINE_DIR=<path> -DWICKED_ENGINE_LIB=<path/to/libWickedEngine.a>

Wicked Engine provides PBR rendering, GPU-based FFT ocean with foam,
multi-cascade wave simulation, and Dear ImGui instrument overlays.
When not available, the existing Irrlicht backend is used.

Keyboard Shortcuts (ImGui HUD)
------------------------------

When the Wicked Engine backend is active, the following keyboard
shortcuts control the instrument HUD overlay:

  F5          Bright Day palette (white backgrounds, high contrast)
  F6          Day palette (dark backgrounds, standard brightness)
  F7          Dusk palette (reduced brightness, warm tones)
  F8          Night palette (black background, red indicators only)
  F9          Toggle layout lock (unlock to drag/resize instruments)
  F10         Toggle depth display units (metres / feet)

Instrument windows: Compass, Speed, Rudder, Depth, Engine, Wind.
Layout and preferences are saved to layout.ini.

